Section : RGB light effect setting (120) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
RGB light effect adjustment test
Before testing, please confirm that 'Legion Lighting Controller' is listed first in the settings-Personalization-Dynamic lighting- Background light control
'Legion Lighting Controller' in list first
1. Check the display on the Legion Space-Device Management-Lighting Themes function page
The page displays normally without garbled characters or error messages
1.1 Please confirm with Project the default state of light efficienc
The default state should be displayed as Mode 1: Current profile Spiral rainbow. Note：After preload, the light effect will remain in the state before preload，Please reset the light effect settings before preloading
1.2 Use Fn+space to switch between different light effect profiles
The current profile will switch the light effect name with the light effect profile Profile 1:Spiral rainbow Profile 2:Blue Profile 3:Ripples Profile 4:Raining Profile 5:Audio Ripple Profile 6:Audio Bounce
2. Adjust the brightness 0-100%
Check if the actual lighting effect will decrease/increase with the adjustment of the brightness bar, resulting in dimming/brightening
3.Click on the 'Lighting Theme Options' button
Successfully entered the 'Lighting Theme Options' page. The page displays normally, with no error messages or garbled text
Note：The lighting effect of the zoomed in image is only a dynamic image, which may have errors compared to the actual lighting effect
Click on the 'Keyboard Lighting' button
The left side will display a keyboard zoom image The keyboard zoom image UI display is consistent with the actual keyboard
Click on the right light effect theme，Switch between different theme effects
The keyboard zoom image Synchronize with the selected lighting effects ,
Click on 'Front Environmental Lighting'button
The left side will display a Front lighting zoom image, The zoom image effect of Front lighting is consistent with the actual keyboard
Click on the right light effect theme，Switch between different theme effects
The zoom image Synchronize with the selected lighting effects ,
Click on 'Rear Environmental Lighting'button
The Rear lighting zoom image will be displayed on the left side, The zoom image effect of Rear lighting is consistent with the actual keyboard
Click on the right light effect theme，Switch between different theme effects
The zoom image Synchronize with the selected lighting effects ,
Click on the 'Logo LED' button
The logo zoom image will be displayed on the left side, The logo lighting zoom image effect is consistent with the actual keyboard
Click on the right light effect theme，Switch between different theme effects
The zoom image Synchronize with the selected lighting effects ,
Switching between different lighting effects using Fn+space
The actual lighting effect will be modified accordingly, and the Fn+space theme will jump accordingly，Only jump to the first 6 fixed topics
Drag and jump to different light icons in the lighting effects theme
The icon displays normally, and the lighting effect can take effect normally
Use the shortcut key Fn+space to switch between different profiles 1-6
The lighting effect can take effect normally, the OSD display is normal, and the page will not lag
Note: When testing the light effect theme, make sure that the sound card driver is the latest to play online music or other audio during the test
The actual light effects and UI renderings appear correctly
Up to 10 custom themes can be set
More than 10 themes‘ The 'Add' button disappears
" Add "user-defined Light area Check
The custom light effect screen is successfully entered. After adding the screen for the first time, start the novice boot to complete the boot process
Custom Light Effect Custom Check
After setting the light effect, the physical keyboard correctly displays the light effect
Click on the 'Keyboard lighting' button above, set keyboard lighting effects, add custom lighting areas, select keyboard areas to set different 'Lighting Zones': set different Lighting effects, set different speeds, and set different directions.
The custom keyboard lighting effect has been successfully set, rendering UI display normal，and the actual keyboard lighting effect is consistent with the UI display
Click on the 'Front Environment Lighting' button above, set the Front lighting effects, add custom lighting areas, select different Front areas to set different 'Lighting Zones': set different Lighting effects, set different speeds, and set different directions.
The custom Front lighting effect has been successfully set,rendering Ui Display normal， and the actual keyboard lighting effect is consistent with the UI display
Click on the 'Rear Environmental Lighting' button above, set the Rear lighting effects, add custom lighting areas, select different Rear areas to set different 'Lighting Zones': set different Lighting effects, set different speeds, and set different directions.
The custom Rear light effect has been successfully set, rendering UI display noarml,and the actual keyboard light effect is consistent with the UI display
Click on the 'Logo LED' button above to set the logo lighting effect and add custom lighting areas: set different lighting effects, set different speeds, and set different directions.
The custom logo light effect has been successfully set, rendering UI display noarml， The actual lighting effect of the keyboard is consistent with the UI display
Deleting Custom Theme
You can correctly delete custom theme effects.
Due to different machine configurations, the behavior of screen light synchronization varies. 1. Without Fin and U lights, when the screen light is projected synchronously, the entire screen is only mapped onto the keyboard. 2. There are Fin lights and U lights, and when the screen light is synchronized, it will be mapped to Fin lights, keyboard, and U lights. 3. Only the U-light, when the screen light is synchronized, it will be mapped to the keyboard and U-light.
The lighting effect mapping is normal
Select the lighting effect as' Lenovo Spectrum sync 'in the lighting themes
Selection successful, switch the lighting theme to 'Lenovo spectrum sync' The 'Keyboard Lighting', 'Front Environmental Lighting', 'Rear Environmental Lighting', and 'Logo LED' on the left side will not be displayed only brightness adjustment option can also be adjusted
Check the screen optical synchronization effect During the test, play the test video in full screen. You are advised to search for the following link video to test: or other 4K HDR video: HDR
The color of the game will be synchronized with the keyboard light effect. Please refer to the left promotional video effect screen light effect will be extended to the keyboard
Use the shortcut keys Fn+↓ or adjust the brightness bar
The lighting effect will become brighter as it darkens

Section : Hotkey and light adjustment coordination check (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Note: The following test items need to be completed according to the actual lighting effect of the machine. The unsupported test items do not need to be executed
RGB Color keyboard light lamp effect
1. Open the Legion space light effect adjustment page and use FN+Space to switch the light effect mode
The OSD display is correct, and the Legion space light effect theme is adjusted synchronously with FN+Space OSD
2. Open the Legion space light effect adjustment page and use FN+↑/FN+↓ to switch the light brightness
The OSD display is correct. The Legion space brightness adjustment is synchronized with FN+↑/FN+↓
3. Open the Legion space light effect adjustment page, and use FN+L to control the Logo indicator switch
The OSD display is correct, and the switch of the Logo indicator is adjusted synchronously with FN+L
4. Open the Legion space light effect adjustment page, and use FN+U to switch the interface indicator
The OSD display is correct, and the switch of the interface indicator is adjusted synchronously with the FN+U
5.2 Switching the Performance Mode to Quiet Mode and then removing the AC
All lights are turned off, the UI rendering changes accordingly, and the brightness decreases to 0%
5.3DC Connects to the AC in quiet mode
Performance mode restores to pre-cut mode, light effect is re-lit, UI rendering is displayed correctly, brightness is restored
5.4 Put the machine in DC balance mode and check the current lighting effect /UI rendering/brightness
Switch to quiet mode, light effect is off /Ui rendering is correct/Brightness is 0%
5.5 The DC Quiet Mode is Switched to the Balanced mode
Light effect restore/render picture UI display correct/brightness restore
6. Connect other external keyboards with bright lights and switch the light effect mode in Legion space
Make sure that the light effect of the physical keyboard is set to the current selected light effect, and the light effect of the rendering is consistent with that of the physical keyboard

Click the 'One Click Configuration' button, or click 'Cancel' button
If you click the 'cancel' button and successfully enter the page, the page will display normally‘ Display a prompt next to 'Lighting Themes','Dynamic lighting background controller' as the first option If you click the 'One click Configuration' button and successfully enter the page, the page will display normally‘ As for the first position of the 'Legion Lighting Controller', the keyboard lighting effect is set to 'Legion Lighting'

1.1 In AC mode, go to S3/S4/S5/Restart
Make sure that light effect adjustment remains user Settings after returning to the system

Make sure that light effect adjustment remains user Settings after returning to the system

1.4 In the DC state, set the Theraml mode to Quiet mode and check the keyboard indicator status
Keyboard light off
1.5 After the AC power is connected again, check the Theraml mode and maintain the quiet mode

Section : uninstall (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
Please conduct this section of testing after completing other tests
Go to Settings, Apps and Features in the Apps module, and uninstall Legion space
1. Uninstall successfully 2.The ‘Legion Lighting Controller’ will be removed from settings - Personalization - Dynamic Light Effects, 3. No files left in the installation directory
Check if the light effect has returned to the default state
After uninstallation, all custom lighting effects under the profile will be restored to default, but the current user's profile status will not be switched. For example, the user switched to Profile 3 and customized it. When uninstalling, profile 3 will be restored to default values, but profile 1 will not be restored.
